Alicia
Oh, yes. So we are.

240
00:18:47,860 --> 00:18:50,260
Latin

241
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,733
I wonder if the embassy
someone can get me a maid.

242
00:18:57,836 --> 00:19:01,237
It's a nice apartment, and I don't mind
dusting and sweeping but I hate cooking.

243
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:03,240
I'll ask them.
And while you're at it,

244
00:19:03,342 --> 00:19:05,902
find out when I go to work,
and on what.
Yes, ma'am.

245
00:19:06,011 --> 00:19:08,605
Waiter Speaking Portuguese
Have another drink?

246
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:12,150
No, thank you. I've had enough.
Oh. Whiskey and soda.

247
00:19:12,251 --> 00:19:14,879
Well, do you hear that?

248
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:17,979
I'm practically on the wagon.
That's quite a change.

249
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:21,821
It's a phase.
You don't think a woman can change?

250
00:19:21,927 --> 00:19:25,522
Sure. But change is fun...
for a while.

251
00:19:25,631 --> 00:19:29,533
For a while.
What a rat you are, Devlin.

252
00:19:29,635 --> 00:19:32,627
All right. You've been
sober for eight days.

253
00:19:32,738 --> 00:19:36,037
As far as I know,
you've made no new conquests.

254
00:19:36,141 --> 00:19:38,041
Well, that's something.

255
00:19:38,143 --> 00:19:41,408
Eight days.
Practically whitewashed.

256
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:46,712
I'm very happy, Dev.
Why won't you let me be happy?

257
00:19:46,818 --> 00:19:49,514
Nobody's stopping you.

258
00:19:52,224 --> 00:19:57,127
Why don't you give that
copper's brain of yours a rest?

259
00:19:57,229 --> 00:20:00,221
Every time you look at me,
I can see it dwelling over its slogans:

260
00:20:00,332 --> 00:20:04,291
"Once a crook, always a crook.
Once a tramp, always a tramp. "

261
00:20:06,338 --> 00:20:08,568
Go on. You can hold my hand.

262
00:20:08,674 --> 00:20:10,972
I won't blackmail you
for it afterwards.

263
00:20:11,076 --> 00:20:12,976
Scared?

264
00:20:13,078 --> 00:20:16,411
I've always been scared
of women, but I get over it.

265
00:20:16,515 --> 00:20:18,710
And now you're scared of yourself.

266
00:20:18,817 --> 00:20:20,910
You're afraid you'll
fall in love with me.

267
00:20:21,019 --> 00:20:24,386
That wouldn't be hard.
Ooh, now, careful, careful.

268
00:20:24,489 --> 00:20:26,616
You enjoy making fun
of me, don't you?

269
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:32,256
No, Dev.
I'm making fun of myself.

270
00:20:32,364 --> 00:20:34,764
I'm pretending I'm a nice,
unspoiled child...

271
00:20:34,866 --> 00:20:37,334
whose heart is full
of daisies and buttercups.

272
00:20:37,436 --> 00:20:40,064
Nice daydream. Than what?

273
00:20:42,941 --> 00:20:44,966
Waiter, Indistinct

274
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:48,103
I think I will have another drink.

275
00:20:48,213 --> 00:20:50,181
I thought you'd get around to it.

276
00:20:50,282 --> 00:20:52,182
Make it a double.

277
00:20:52,284 --> 00:20:55,151
Devlin Orders In Portuguese

278
00:20:57,522 --> 00:21:00,616
Why won't you believe in me, Dev?

279
00:21:02,027 --> 00:21:03,927
Just a little.

280
00:21:06,698 --> 00:21:08,632
Why won't you?

281
00:21:21,146 --> 00:21:24,047
I know why you won't, Dev.
You're sore.

282
00:21:24,149 --> 00:21:27,050
You're sore because you've
fallen for a little drunk...

283
00:21:27,152 --> 00:21:29,746
you tailed in Miami,
and you don't like it.

284
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:31,982
Makes you sick all over,
doesn't it?

285
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:35,059
People will laugh at you, the invincible
Devlin in love with someone...

286
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,424
who isn't worth
even wasting the words on.

287
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:41,090
Poor Dev, in love with a no-good gal.
It must be awful. I'm sorry

288
00:21:42,934 --> 00:21:45,232
Car Horns Honking

289
00:21:45,337 --> 00:21:48,306
Gentlemen, I assure you
she's a perfect type for the job.

290
00:21:48,407 --> 00:21:51,706
It's not the girl. It's this
German scientist I'm worried about.

291
00:21:51,810 --> 00:21:55,644
I simply question why we don't find
some way of taking them into custody.

292
00:21:55,747 --> 00:21:58,773
It'd do no good. Even if we arrested
their leader Alexander Sebastian,

293
00:21:58,884 --> 00:22:01,751
tomorrow another Farben man
takes his place and their work goes on.

294
00:22:01,853 --> 00:22:06,290
Yes, you're right. I see, Captain
Prescott, your method is the best way.

295
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:09,224
Well, she's good at making
friends with gentlemen,

296
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:12,058
and we want somebody inside
his house, in his confidence.

297
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:14,394
You have faith in this procedure,
Captain Prescott?

298
00:22:14,499 --> 00:22:16,399
Oh, yes.
With somebody on the inside

299
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:18,594
Have you consulted the young lady?
No, not yet.

300
00:22:18,704 --> 00:22:21,935
As a matter of fact, our man Devlin just
brought here down here the other day.

301
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:24,406
Now we're waiting for Sebastian
to come back to Rio.

302
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:26,909
Has your Mr. Devlin told her
the nature of the work?

303
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:30,880
No, we haven't discussed it
with him at all. But I can set
your mind at rest about her.

304
00:22:30,982 --> 00:22:34,076
You're sure of her political side?
Oh, oh, yes.

305
00:22:34,186 --> 00:22:38,418
Well, there is nothing to be lost
if we proceed as you advise.

306
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:41,856
Now, that's fine. I'll give Devlin
his instructions right away.

307
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:43,752
It's nice out here.

308
00:23:43,855 --> 00:23:47,951
Let's not go out for dinner.
Let's stay here.

309
00:23:48,059 --> 00:23:50,254
We have to eat.

310
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:54,093
We can eat here.
I'll cook.

311
00:23:54,199 --> 00:23:57,259
I thought you didn't
like to cook.

312
00:23:57,369 --> 00:23:59,929
No, I don't like to cook.

313
00:24:01,706 --> 00:24:04,971
But I have a chicken in the icebox,
and you're eating it.

314
00:24:05,076 --> 00:24:07,442
What about all the washing up
afterward?

315
00:24:07,546 --> 00:24:09,844
We'll eat it with our fingers.

316
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:11,882
Don't we need any plates?

317
00:24:11,983 --> 00:24:15,350
Yes. One for you and one for me.

318
00:24:18,690 --> 00:24:21,784
Mind if I have dinner
with you tonight?

319
00:24:21,893 --> 00:24:24,418
I'd be delighted.

320
00:24:24,529 --> 00:24:27,259
Where are you going?
Well, if we're going to stay in,

321
00:24:27,365 --> 00:24:30,425
I have to telephone the hotel,
see if there are any messages.

322
00:24:30,535 --> 00:24:33,504
You have to?
I have to.

323
00:24:43,381 --> 00:24:45,645
Dialing Phone

324
00:24:45,750 --> 00:24:48,913
This is a very strange
love affair.

325
00:24:49,020 --> 00:24:51,181
Why?

326
00:24:51,289 --> 00:24:54,554
Maybe the fact
that you don't love me.

327
00:24:55,794 --> 00:24:59,924
Hello? Palace Hotel?
Parle Anglais?

328
00:25:00,031 --> 00:25:03,694
This is T.R. Devlin.
Are there any messages for me?

329
00:25:03,802 --> 00:25:06,669
When I don't love you,
I'll let you know.

330
00:25:06,771 --> 00:25:08,705
You haven't said anything.

331
00:25:08,807 --> 00:25:11,571
Actions speak louder than words.
Chuckling

332
00:25:11,676 --> 00:25:14,668
There is? Good.
Read it to me, please.

333
00:25:24,823 --> 00:25:27,257
Prescott wants me over
right away.

334
00:25:27,359 --> 00:25:30,123
Did he say what about?
No.

335
00:25:30,228 --> 00:25:33,026
Maybe it's our assignment.
Probably.

336
00:25:41,673 --> 00:25:43,903
Do you want me to bring
anything back with me?

337
00:25:44,009 --> 00:25:48,912
Yes. What about a nice bottle of wine?
We'll celebrate.

338
00:25:49,014 --> 00:25:51,539
What time shall I come back?

339
00:25:51,650 --> 00:25:53,641
Seven o'clock.

340
00:25:57,522 --> 00:25:59,854
Goodbye.
Goodbye.

341
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:20,540
Prescott What is it, Devlin?
What's the matter?

342
00:26:20,645 --> 00:26:22,875
I don't know if she'll do it.
What do you mean,
you don't think she'd

343
00:26:22,981 --> 00:26:26,109
You haven't discussed it
with her, have you?
I didn't know what the job was.

344
00:26:26,217 --> 00:26:28,378
Well, what do you mean,
she wouldn't do it?

345
00:26:28,486 --> 00:26:31,751
Well, I don't think she's that type
of woman. She strikes me as being

346
00:26:31,856 --> 00:26:33,881
I don't understand your attitude.

347
00:26:33,992 --> 00:26:37,325
Why do you think she won't do it?
Well, she's had no experience.

348
00:26:37,429 --> 00:26:41,195
Oh, come now. What experience
does she lack, do you think?

349
00:26:41,299 --> 00:26:44,268
She's never been trained for that
kind of work. They'll see through her.

350
00:26:44,369 --> 00:26:46,894
Miss Huberman was chosen
not only because her father...

351
00:26:47,005 --> 00:26:49,599
gives her an ideal background,
but because Sebastian knows her.

352
00:26:51,643 --> 00:26:53,975
Oh, yes. He was once
in love with her.

353
00:26:56,414 --> 00:26:58,314
Oh, I didn't know that.

354
00:26:58,416 --> 00:27:00,941
I don't see why we're arguing
about petty things like this.

355
00:27:01,052 --> 00:27:03,953
We've got important work to do.
Sebastian's house is a cover-up...

356
00:27:04,055 --> 00:27:06,353
for whatever this Farben
group's up to here in Rio.

357
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:10,451
We've got to get Miss Huberman
inside that house and find out
what's going on there.

358
00:27:10,562 --> 00:27:13,998
So I think you'd better go back
to Miss Huberman and explain
to her what she has to do.

359
00:27:14,099 --> 00:27:16,363
I, uh
Well, what is it?

360
00:27:16,468 --> 00:27:19,995
Nothing, sir.
Oh, I thought you were
going to say something.

361
00:27:20,105 --> 00:27:23,336
How is the meeting to be arranged?
Oh, well, we've discussed that.

362
00:27:23,441 --> 00:27:26,239
I think the riding club
would be the best place.

363
00:27:26,344 --> 00:27:29,211
Sebastian usually
rides there in the mornings.

364
00:27:29,314 --> 00:27:32,977
So the rest is up to you
and Miss Huberman.

365
00:27:33,084 --> 00:27:36,850
Okay, Devlin, that's all.
All right.

366
00:27:42,260 --> 00:27:44,694
Door Closes

367
00:27:49,167 --> 00:27:51,897
Alicia Dev, is that you?
Uh-huh.

368
00:27:52,003 --> 00:27:55,439
I'm glad you're late. This chicken
took longer than I expected.

369
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:59,442
What did they say?
Hope it isn't done too much.

370
00:27:59,544 --> 00:28:01,842
It caught fire once.

371
00:28:01,946 --> 00:28:05,143
I think it's better
if I cut it up out here.

372
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:08,310
Unless you want a half a one
to yourself. Chuckles

373
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:10,980
We're going to have
knives and forks after all.

374
00:28:11,089 --> 00:28:13,284
I've decided we're
going to eat in style.

375
00:28:13,391 --> 00:28:17,760
Marriage must be wonderful with this
sort of thing going on every day.

376
00:28:19,631 --> 00:28:22,464
I wonder if it's too cold out here.
Maybe we should eat inside.

377
00:28:28,339 --> 00:28:31,069
Hasn't something like this
happened before?

378
00:28:34,145 --> 00:28:36,875
What's the matter?

379
00:28:36,981 --> 00:28:39,882
Don't look so tense.
Troubles?

380
00:28:41,486 --> 00:28:44,353
Well, handsome, I think you'd better
tell mama what's going on.

381
00:28:44,456 --> 00:28:47,721
All this secrecy's going
to ruin my little dinner.

382
00:28:47,826 --> 00:28:51,592
Come on, Mr. D.,
what is darkening your brow?

383
00:28:51,696 --> 00:28:54,494
After dinner.
No, now.

384
00:28:56,234 --> 00:28:58,702
Look, I'll make it easy for you.
The time has come...

385
00:28:58,803 --> 00:29:02,000
when you must tell me that you have
a wife and two adorable children...

386
00:29:02,107 --> 00:29:05,304
and this madness between us
can't go on any longer.

387
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:08,243
I'll bet you've heard
that line often enough.

388
00:29:11,182 --> 00:29:16,745
Right below the belt every time.
Oh, that isn't fair, Dev.

389
00:29:16,855 --> 00:29:21,087
Skip it. We have other things
to talk about. We've got a job.

390
00:29:22,627 --> 00:29:24,527
Oh. So there is a job.

391
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:29,594
You, uh You remember
a man named Sebastian?

392
00:29:31,736 --> 00:29:34,330
Alex Sebastian?
Yes.

393
00:29:34,439 --> 00:29:36,532
One of my father's friends, yes.

394
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:39,876
He had quite a crush on you.

395
00:29:39,978 --> 00:29:41,946
I wasn't very responsive.

396
00:29:44,315 --> 00:29:47,182
Well, he's here. The head
of a large German business concern.

397
00:29:47,285 --> 00:29:49,378
His family always had money.

398
00:29:49,487 --> 00:29:52,786
He's part of the combine that
built up the German war machine
and hopes to keep on going.

399
00:29:52,891 --> 00:29:56,292
Something big?
It has all the earmarks
of being something big.

400
00:29:56,394 --> 00:29:58,521
We have to contact him.

401
00:30:15,046 --> 00:30:17,207
Go on.
Let's have all of it.

402
00:30:17,315 --> 00:30:20,910
We're meeting him tomorrow.
The rest is up to you.

403
00:30:21,019 --> 00:30:23,783
You've got to work on him
and land him.

404
00:30:23,888 --> 00:30:28,086
Mata Hari.
She makes love for the papers.

405
00:30:28,193 --> 00:30:31,287
There are no papers.
You land him.

406
00:30:31,396 --> 00:30:33,830
Find out what's going on
inside his house,

407
00:30:33,932 --> 00:30:36,924
what the group around him
is up to, and report to us.

408
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:42,436
I suppose you knew about this pretty
little job of mine all the time.

409
00:30:42,540 --> 00:30:46,340
No. I only just
found out about it.

410
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:50,314
Did you say anything?

411
00:30:50,415 --> 00:30:54,112
I mean, that maybe I wasn't
the girl for such shenanigans?

412
00:30:56,221 --> 00:30:58,382
I figured that was up to you.

413
00:30:58,489 --> 00:31:00,923
If you'd care to back out
I suppose you told them,

414
00:31:01,025 --> 00:31:04,051
"Alicia Huberman will have this
Sebastian eating out of her
hand in a couple of weeks.

415
00:31:04,162 --> 00:31:07,359
She's good at that. Always was. "
I didn't say anything.

416
00:31:10,168 --> 00:31:15,196
Not a word for that little
lovesick lady you left an hour ago?

417
00:31:16,941 --> 00:31:18,966
I told you,
that's the assignment.

418
00:31:19,077 --> 00:31:21,910
Oh, well, now,
don't get sore, Dev.

419
00:31:23,514 --> 00:31:27,951
I'm only fishing for
a little bird call from my dream man.

420
00:31:29,787 --> 00:31:31,914
One little remark such as,

421
00:31:32,023 --> 00:31:35,424
"How dare you gentlemen
suggest that Alicia Huberman

422
00:31:35,526 --> 00:31:39,462
the new Miss Huberman
be submitted to so ugly a fate?"

423
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:41,930
That's not funny.

424
00:31:46,871 --> 00:31:49,431
Do you want me to take the job?

425
00:31:49,540 --> 00:31:52,907
You're answering for yourself.
I am asking you.

426
00:31:53,011 --> 00:31:55,002
It's up to you.

427
00:31:56,547 --> 00:31:58,447
Not a peep, hmm?

428
00:32:00,919 --> 00:32:03,854
Oh, darling, what you didn't
tell them, tell me

429
00:32:03,955 --> 00:32:07,789
that you believe I'm nice and that
I love you and I'll never change back.

430
00:32:09,994 --> 00:32:12,155
I'm waiting for your answer.

431
00:32:17,302 --> 00:32:19,463
What a little pal you are.

432
00:32:22,540 --> 00:32:26,101
Never believing me, hmm?
Not a word of faith.

433
00:32:26,210 --> 00:32:29,805
Just down the drain with Alicia.
That's where she belongs.

434
00:32:31,416 --> 00:32:34,817
Oh, Dev, Dev.

435
00:32:45,496 --> 00:32:47,521
When do I go to work
for Uncle Sam?

436
00:32:47,632 --> 00:32:49,623
Tomorrow morning.

437
00:33:01,112 --> 00:33:05,378
Oh, we shouldn't have had this out here.
It's all cold now.

438
00:33:06,751 --> 00:33:08,776
What are you looking for?

439
00:33:08,886 --> 00:33:11,878
I had a bottle of champagne.
I must have left it somewhere.

440
00:33:22,033 --> 00:33:24,900
In case you're asked,
I'm with Pan American Airways.

441
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:28,564
As Devlin?
Yes. Public relations office.

442
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:30,732
Anything else?

443
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:33,538
No, except we met on the plane
coming in from Miami.

444
00:33:33,644 --> 00:33:35,737
Less detail, the better.

445
00:33:47,492 --> 00:33:50,120
Are you sure that's him?
Yes.

446
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:52,856
We'll go by him easy,
let him spot you. Come on.

447
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:25,151
I guess I'm the girl
nobody remembers.

448
00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:27,231
Was it Sebastian?
Yes.

449
00:34:27,331 --> 00:34:29,891
We'll stick around,
give him another chance.

450
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:55,582
Bell Ringing

451
00:34:58,629 --> 00:35:01,530
Orchestral

452
00:35:16,647 --> 00:35:19,548
My dear Alicia, will you
forgive me for being late?

453
00:35:19,650 --> 00:35:22,551
Last minute conference at the office.
You got my message?

454
00:35:22,653 --> 00:35:25,383
Yes. It's all right, Alex.
Sweet of you to wait.

455
00:35:25,490 --> 00:35:28,653
I was afraid you might run on.
Oh, I'm not that easily put off.

456
00:35:28,759 --> 00:35:31,057
I was too anxious
to meet you again.

457
00:35:31,162 --> 00:35:33,255
You know, I'm tired.

458
00:35:33,364 --> 00:35:36,856
The worst thing about business
is it makes you feel old and look old.

459
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:39,732
You seem to have escaped
all of that.

460
00:35:39,837 --> 00:35:42,567
Four years of dullness
and disintegration. Awful.

461
00:35:42,673 --> 00:35:45,233
Alex, you look younger
than you did in Washington.

462
00:35:45,343 --> 00:35:48,870
Well, it's a temporary improvement,
entirely due to your presence, my dear.

463
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:51,448
You always affected me like a tonic.

464
00:35:51,549 --> 00:35:54,074
Perhaps now
with you here in Rio

465
00:35:54,185 --> 00:35:57,086
unless you insist
on running away from me again

466
00:35:57,188 --> 00:35:59,713
Oh, uh, would you like
another drink?

467
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:02,725
Yes. Thank you.
Deux martinis.

468
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:11,125
You know him?

469
00:36:11,235 --> 00:36:13,863
No, I don't think so.
But he seems familiar.

470
00:36:13,971 --> 00:36:15,871
Captain Prescott,
intelligence man.

471
00:36:15,973 --> 00:36:17,998
He's down here as part
of a Washington espionage.

