704
00:50:38,335 --> 00:50:41,031
Don't talk like that.
I detest him.

705
00:50:41,138 --> 00:50:44,232
Really?
He's very good-looking.

706
00:50:44,341 --> 00:50:49,040
Alex, I've told you before.
Mr. Devlin doesn't mean a thing to me.

707
00:50:49,146 --> 00:50:51,979
I'd like to be convinced.

708
00:50:52,082 --> 00:50:56,849
Would you maybe care to convince me,
Alicia, that Mr. Devlin
means nothing to you?

709
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:01,115
Car Horn Honks

710
00:51:01,224 --> 00:51:04,682
...pleased to hear, Senor Barbosa, that
our little theatrical plan is working.

711
00:51:04,795 --> 00:51:07,127
We've got hold of something
concrete for a change.

712
00:51:07,230 --> 00:51:09,323
I'm delighted, gentlemen.
What is it?

713
00:51:09,433 --> 00:51:12,459
Professor Wilhelm Otto Rensler
is working here in Brazil.

714
00:51:12,569 --> 00:51:15,697
One of Germany's scientific wizards.
I didn't know he was here.

715
00:51:15,806 --> 00:51:18,775
Oh, yes. He's living
and experimenting in Sebastian's house.

716
00:51:18,875 --> 00:51:21,139
They call him Dr. Anderson.
Knocking

717
00:51:21,244 --> 00:51:23,144
Entree.

718
00:51:23,246 --> 00:51:28,274
Excuse me, sir. Miss Huberman wishes
to see Captain Prescott or Mr. Devlin.

719
00:51:28,385 --> 00:51:30,910
What do you mean? She's here?
Yes, sir.

720
00:51:31,021 --> 00:51:33,489
Beardsley
Well, show her in, Ribiero.
Yes, sir.

721
00:51:33,590 --> 00:51:35,922
I don't like this.
I don't like her coming here.

722
00:51:36,026 --> 00:51:39,154
She's had me worried for some time.
A woman of that sort.

723
00:51:41,865 --> 00:51:43,924
What sort is that,
Mr. Beardsley?

724
00:51:44,034 --> 00:51:46,969
Oh, I don't think any of us have
any illusions about her character,
have we, Devlin?

725
00:51:47,070 --> 00:51:48,970
Not at all,
not the slightest.

726
00:51:49,072 --> 00:51:52,337
Miss Huberman is first,
last and always not a lady.

727
00:51:52,442 --> 00:51:55,605
She may be risking her life,
but when it comes to being a lady,

728
00:51:55,712 --> 00:51:58,647
she doesn't hold a candle
to your wife, sir,

729
00:51:58,748 --> 00:52:02,206
sitting in Washington playing
bridge with three other ladies
of great honor and virtue.

730
00:52:02,319 --> 00:52:04,446
Take it easy, Dev.
Sorry.

731
00:52:04,554 --> 00:52:06,954
I think those remarks
about my wife are uncalled-for.

732
00:52:07,057 --> 00:52:10,584
Withdrawn. Apologized, sir.
Door Opens

733
00:52:13,997 --> 00:52:16,158
How do you do, Miss Huberman?
How do you do?

734
00:52:16,266 --> 00:52:19,235
This is Mr. Beardsley
and Senor Julio Barbosa.

735
00:52:19,336 --> 00:52:21,304
Care to sit down?
Thank you.

736
00:52:21,404 --> 00:52:23,872
You have the esteem
of my government, senorita.

737
00:52:23,974 --> 00:52:26,169
But we are worried
about your visiting this office.

738
00:52:26,276 --> 00:52:30,178
I promise not to break the rules
again, but I need some advice
and I couldn't find Mr. Devlin.

739
00:52:30,280 --> 00:52:32,646
In fact, I need it before lunch.

740
00:52:32,749 --> 00:52:34,740
Something happened?

741
00:52:34,851 --> 00:52:37,319
Yes, something
rather confusing.

742
00:52:37,420 --> 00:52:40,321
Mr. Sebastian
has asked me to marry him.

743
00:52:40,423 --> 00:52:42,516
What?
Well, well.

744
00:52:42,626 --> 00:52:45,527
He, he wants me
to marry him right away,

745
00:52:45,629 --> 00:52:48,530
and I am to give him
my answer at lunch.

746
00:52:48,632 --> 00:52:51,760
But I didn't know what the department
might think about such a step.

747
00:52:51,868 --> 00:52:55,201
Are you willing to go this
far for us, Miss Huberman?

748
00:52:56,873 --> 00:52:59,034
Yes, if you wish.

749
00:52:59,142 --> 00:53:01,303
What do you think of this, Devlin?

750
00:53:03,213 --> 00:53:05,408
Oh, I think it's a useful idea.

751
00:53:05,515 --> 00:53:09,144
Well, you know the situation
better than any of us.

752
00:53:09,252 --> 00:53:12,551
May I ask what inspired
Alex Sebastian to go this far?

753
00:53:12,656 --> 00:53:15,318
He's in love with me.

754
00:53:15,425 --> 00:53:18,326
And he thinks
you're in love with him?

755
00:53:19,963 --> 00:53:23,057
Yes, that's what he thinks.

756
00:53:23,166 --> 00:53:25,726
Barbosa
Gentlemen, it's the cream of the jest.

757
00:53:29,239 --> 00:53:32,538
Then
Then it's all right?

758
00:53:33,677 --> 00:53:36,874
Well, yes. I'd, I'd say so.

759
00:53:36,980 --> 00:53:40,973
Of course, it's
a perfect marriage... for us.

760
00:53:41,084 --> 00:53:43,575
There's only one thing.
Won't it delay us a bit?

761
00:53:43,687 --> 00:53:45,746
Prescott
What do you mean?

762
00:53:45,855 --> 00:53:49,484
Well, Mr. Sebastian is a very romantic
fellow, isn't he, Alicia?

763
00:53:49,593 --> 00:53:51,686
Yes.

764
00:53:51,795 --> 00:53:55,788
Then he'll probably want to take
his bride away for a long honeymoon.

765
00:53:55,899 --> 00:53:58,697
Won't that hold us up?
Devlin's got a point there.

766
00:53:58,802 --> 00:54:01,396
Oh, I don't know. I think
we can rely on Miss Huberman...

767
00:54:01,504 --> 00:54:04,496
to get back
into the house quickly.

768
00:54:04,608 --> 00:54:07,168
Yes, I think I can manage that.

769
00:54:08,545 --> 00:54:11,036
Well, everything seems
to be nicely arranged.

770
00:54:11,147 --> 00:54:14,548
I don't think you need me here anymore,
do you, Captain Prescott?

771
00:54:14,651 --> 00:54:18,678
I do want to thank you,
Miss Huberman, very much.

772
00:54:18,788 --> 00:54:22,884
I think so far everything has been
managed with great intelligence.

773
00:54:22,993 --> 00:54:25,257
Barbosa
Yes. Thank you very much.

774
00:54:25,362 --> 00:54:28,456
Are you quite sure she didn't
come down here to see you?

775
00:54:28,565 --> 00:54:31,227
To capture the rich
Alex Sebastian for a husband?

776
00:54:31,334 --> 00:54:33,894
Don't be absurd, Mother.
She didn't even know I was here.

777
00:54:34,004 --> 00:54:36,529
We will discuss it
more fully tonight.

778
00:54:36,640 --> 00:54:39,040
We will not discuss it tonight.

779
00:54:43,847 --> 00:54:47,408
All these carping questions are merely
the expression of your own jealousy,

780
00:54:47,517 --> 00:54:50,577
just as you've always
been jealous of any woman
I've ever shown any interest in.

781
00:54:50,687 --> 00:54:52,882
In this case, there's
nothing more to discuss.

782
00:54:52,989 --> 00:54:55,856
You mean, then, you are
going ahead with this marriage?

783
00:54:57,360 --> 00:55:00,227
I mean that the wedding
will be next week.

784
00:55:00,330 --> 00:55:02,389
It'll be private.

785
00:55:02,499 --> 00:55:06,367
We shall both be pleased
to have you present, if you wish.

786
00:55:30,360 --> 00:55:32,726
Knocking At Door

787
00:55:36,166 --> 00:55:38,225
Oh.

788
00:55:38,335 --> 00:55:41,304
Good evening, sir. Madame.
Good evening, Joseph.

789
00:55:41,404 --> 00:55:45,636
Joseph. Joseph, it doesn't look
very cheerful in here.

790
00:55:45,742 --> 00:55:48,711
I'm sorry, sir. Madame Sebastian
wasn't certain you'd be back tonight.

791
00:55:48,812 --> 00:55:50,712
Why not?
I telegraphed her.

792
00:55:50,814 --> 00:55:53,874
Madame Sebastian said
we were all to retire, sir.

793
00:55:53,983 --> 00:55:57,919
Where is my mother?
Madame Sebastian
went to bed very early, sir.

794
00:55:58,021 --> 00:56:01,787
I'm sorry, my dear. I'm afraid this
isn't a very bright homecoming for you.

795
00:56:01,891 --> 00:56:04,086
That's all right, Alex.
Well, what shall we do?

796
00:56:04,194 --> 00:56:06,560
Shall we have Joseph arrange
a little food for us?

797
00:56:06,663 --> 00:56:09,188
Not unless you want to.
I'm rather tired myself.

798
00:56:09,299 --> 00:56:11,563
We'll go right up, then?
Good night.

799
00:56:11,668 --> 00:56:13,568
Good night, madame.

800
00:56:16,973 --> 00:56:19,806
I'd like to have all my dresses
put out on the beds here.

801
00:56:19,909 --> 00:56:22,707
Don't hang anything up.
I'd like to know where everything goes.

802
00:56:22,812 --> 00:56:25,872
Oh, Joseph, would you
have the closets aired?
Yes, madame.

803
00:56:30,987 --> 00:56:34,388
Oh, this isn't very large.
I'll need more room.

804
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:47,401
This door is locked.
That's used for a storeroom, madame.

805
00:56:47,504 --> 00:56:49,802
Oh. May I have the key?

806
00:56:49,906 --> 00:56:52,670
I do not have the keys, madame.
Where are they?

807
00:56:52,776 --> 00:56:56,041
Madame Sebastian has charge
of all the house keys, madame.

808
00:56:57,380 --> 00:56:59,314
Oh.

809
00:56:59,416 --> 00:57:01,782
Do you know
where Mr. Sebastian is?

810
00:57:01,885 --> 00:57:05,946
I believe he is having a business
meeting downstairs in the study, madame.

811
00:57:08,091 --> 00:57:12,255
I miss Hupka. He was
a first-class metallurgist.

812
00:57:12,362 --> 00:57:14,592
Leykin is just as good.

813
00:57:14,697 --> 00:57:17,564
Such is your opinion.
But I don't want to criticize.

814
00:57:17,667 --> 00:57:21,763
What, uh, were you asking?
Oh, you want a report.

815
00:57:21,871 --> 00:57:25,272
A written report.
Well, my friends,

816
00:57:25,375 --> 00:57:27,468
my work is done.

817
00:57:27,577 --> 00:57:30,808
You've been successful.
Yes.

818
00:57:38,154 --> 00:57:41,214
Oh, I'm very sorry. I
Not at all. Come on in.

819
00:57:41,324 --> 00:57:44,225
No. I'm sorry to interrupt you.
I didn't know you were busy.

820
00:57:44,327 --> 00:57:47,558
Some of the closets are locked.
Could you give me the keys?

821
00:57:47,664 --> 00:57:50,224
Oh, I'm so sorry.
I'd forgotten about the keys.

822
00:57:50,333 --> 00:57:53,325
Of course.
I'll get them for you at once.

823
00:58:00,009 --> 00:58:03,467
I'll bring the keys to you
right away, my dear.

824
00:58:03,580 --> 00:58:06,879
Light Knocking
Mother? Mother?

825
00:58:06,983 --> 00:58:09,213
Mrs. Sebastian
Come in.

826
00:58:09,319 --> 00:58:11,753
Door Opens, Closes

827
00:58:11,855 --> 00:58:14,323
Sebastian
Mother, Alicia wants the keys
to get into the closets.

828
00:58:14,424 --> 00:58:17,621
Mrs. Sebastian
I think they can be safer
left to me. After all

829
00:58:17,727 --> 00:58:20,127
Sebastian
Please, Mother, stop arguing!
Give me those keys!

830
00:58:20,230 --> 00:58:23,131
Mrs. Sebastian
I will not. You won't get
these keys, and that's that.

831
00:58:23,233 --> 00:58:27,465
Sebastian
Mother, will you please
give me the keys? Thank you.

832
00:58:37,814 --> 00:58:40,009
Well, here they are.

833
00:58:40,116 --> 00:58:43,449
Afraid I'm going to be busy
for the rest of the morning,
my dear.

834
00:58:43,553 --> 00:58:46,454
See you at lunch.
Thank you, dear.

835
00:59:00,937 --> 00:59:03,633
Mr. Sebastian
has the key for this, madame.

836
00:59:03,740 --> 00:59:05,731
It's the wine cellar.

837
00:59:18,285 --> 00:59:21,345
Well, then, the wine cellar
is the obvious place to look.

838
00:59:21,454 --> 00:59:24,480
Car Horns Honking
Alex has the key to that.

839
00:59:24,591 --> 00:59:26,491
Then get it from him.

840
00:59:26,593 --> 00:59:28,788
Get it? How?

841
00:59:28,895 --> 00:59:31,125
Don't you live hear him?

842
00:59:32,766 --> 00:59:35,030
What do I look for
if I get the key?

843
00:59:35,135 --> 00:59:39,003
You look for a bottle of wine,
like the one that rattled
the fellow at dinner that night.

844
00:59:39,105 --> 00:59:42,734
All the bottles look alike to me.
I'm no mastermind.

845
00:59:42,842 --> 00:59:45,242
You're doing all right.

846
00:59:48,048 --> 00:59:50,073
It's no fun, Dev.

847
00:59:51,818 --> 00:59:54,548
Too late for that now,
isn't it?

848
00:59:54,654 --> 00:59:59,216
Look, uh, why don't you persuade
your husband to throw a large shindig...

849
00:59:59,326 --> 01:00:03,285
so that he can introduce his bride
to Rio society, say sometime next week?

850
01:00:03,396 --> 01:00:06,058
Why?
Consider me invited,

851
01:00:06,166 --> 01:00:09,727
and I'll try and find out
about that wine cellar business.

852
01:00:11,471 --> 01:00:16,374
I don't think my husband is
interested in entertaining just yet.

853
01:00:16,476 --> 01:00:19,206
The honeymoon isn't over, huh?

854
01:00:21,014 --> 01:00:23,414
Don't underestimate
your charms, Mrs. Sebastian.

855
01:00:23,516 --> 01:00:25,416
You can handle it.

856
01:00:25,518 --> 01:00:27,748
I don't think it's going
to be so easy about you.

857
01:00:27,854 --> 01:00:29,754
He thinks
you're in love with me.

858
01:00:29,856 --> 01:00:32,757
Well, then tell him you thought
if you invited me to the house...

859
01:00:32,859 --> 01:00:35,293
and I saw
how happily married you were,

860
01:00:35,395 --> 01:00:39,422
then the horrid passion I have
for you might be torn out of me.

861
01:00:39,532 --> 01:00:41,557
That sounds very logical.

862
01:00:41,668 --> 01:00:43,932
Good. Next week, then,
and get the key.

863
01:00:44,037 --> 01:00:47,666
I have to fly up to Berlin,
but I'll be back in time.

864
01:00:47,774 --> 01:00:49,674
All right.

865
01:00:49,776 --> 01:00:52,006
I'll be looking forward
to seeing you.

866
01:00:52,112 --> 01:00:54,512
It's always a pleasure
meeting you, madame.

867
01:01:31,251 --> 01:01:33,651
Sebastian I'm surprised
at Mr. Devlin coming tonight.

868
01:01:33,753 --> 01:01:37,245
I don't blame anyone for being
in love with you, darling.

869
01:01:37,357 --> 01:01:42,454
Il just hope that nothing will happen
to give him any false impression.

870
01:01:42,562 --> 01:01:44,757
I'll be with you in a minute.

871
01:01:54,207 --> 01:01:56,107
Darling.

872
01:01:59,913 --> 01:02:02,381
It's not that I don't trust you,
but when you're in love at my age,

873
01:02:02,482 --> 01:02:04,382
every man who looks
at a woman is a menace.

874
01:02:04,484 --> 01:02:07,612
Will you forgive me
for even talking about it?

875
01:02:07,720 --> 01:02:10,086
I'm very contrite.

876
01:02:22,836 --> 01:02:45,391
Orchestra: Waltz
Guests Chattering

877
01:02:45,426 --> 01:03:07,912
Orchestra: Waltz
Guests Chattering

878
01:03:07,947 --> 01:03:10,677
Well, I think we might join
the rest of the party now.

879
01:03:10,783 --> 01:03:13,843
I think all our guests are here.

880
01:03:21,494 --> 01:03:23,553
Where can I find Alex Sebastian?

881
01:03:23,663 --> 01:03:26,063
By the drawing room, sir.
Thanks.

882
01:03:42,749 --> 01:03:44,649
Hello, Dev.
Good evening.

883
01:03:53,226 --> 01:03:55,319
You haven't seen the house,
have you?

884
01:03:55,428 --> 01:03:57,328
Well, it's quite
a jolly, little cottage.

885
01:03:57,430 --> 01:03:59,330
Let me show you
around the place.

886
01:03:59,432 --> 01:04:01,559
Later.
He's on the trail.

887
01:04:04,370 --> 01:04:06,531
Devlin, glad to see you.
Good evening.

888
01:04:06,639 --> 01:04:08,800
It was kind of your bride
to invite me.

889
01:04:08,908 --> 01:04:12,969
We both invited you, Mr. Devlin. See
that our guest is fed, my dear, amused.

890
01:04:13,079 --> 01:04:16,173
You know what
Oh, excuse me.

891
01:04:16,282 --> 01:04:18,682
Madame Esterich,
I'm so glad to see you.

892
01:04:21,854 --> 01:04:24,687
This isn't going to be easy.
Why?

893
01:04:24,791 --> 01:04:27,021
He, uh... he's quite sensitive
about you.

894
01:04:27,126 --> 01:04:29,253
He's going to watch us
like a hawk.

895
01:04:29,362 --> 01:04:32,024
Yes, he's rather jealous
of anyone.

896
01:04:32,131 --> 01:04:34,361
Where'd you get the key,
off his chain?

897
01:04:34,467 --> 01:04:36,367
Yes.

898
01:04:36,469 --> 01:04:40,428
Let's hope the liquor doesn't run out
and start him down the cellar for more.

899
01:04:40,540 --> 01:04:43,168
Oh, I hadn't thought about that.
Quite a point.

900
01:04:47,714 --> 01:04:49,614
Thank you.

901
01:04:49,716 --> 01:04:51,741
Oh, Mr. Devlin. How nice.
You remember me?

902
01:04:51,851 --> 01:04:55,116
Senora Ortiz.
How sweet. Young men
usually have short memories.

903
01:04:55,221 --> 01:04:57,781
Oh, here's something I adore
champagne.

904
01:04:57,890 --> 01:04:59,790
Chuckling
Oh, may I?

905
01:05:07,634 --> 01:05:09,465
Cork Pops
Joseph?

906
01:05:09,569 --> 01:05:12,970
Madame?
Do you think you have enough
champagne to last the evening?

907
01:05:13,072 --> 01:05:15,632
I don't know, madame.
I hope so.

908
01:05:33,326 --> 01:05:35,624
Enjoying yourself, Mr. Devlin?
Very much, thank you.

909
01:05:35,728 --> 01:05:38,128
There's so many things I would
like to ask about the States.

910
01:05:38,231 --> 01:05:41,723
I haven't heard anything
for a long time.
I'll be glad to tell you.

911
01:05:41,834 --> 01:05:44,325
Will you excuse me?
Would you mind?

912
01:05:44,437 --> 01:05:46,337
Certainly.

913
01:05:57,150 --> 01:05:59,141
Laughing

914
01:06:00,520 --> 01:06:02,420
We better hurry.
Lots of time.

915
01:06:02,522 --> 01:06:05,116
No, Joseph might have
to ask Alex for more wine.

916
01:06:05,224 --> 01:06:07,249
Uh-huh.
Hmm.

917
01:06:07,360 --> 01:06:10,955
He's running out
faster than he thought.
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

918
01:06:11,064 --> 01:06:13,726
Laughing Continues
Is he, uh, watching?

919
01:06:13,833 --> 01:06:16,131
Yes. You'd better go out
in the garden alone...

920
01:06:16,235 --> 01:06:19,671
and wait around back of the house for me
and I'll show you the wine cellar door.

921
01:06:30,783 --> 01:06:33,513
Nice party, isn't it?
It's a wonderful party.

922
01:06:33,619 --> 01:06:36,247
And you're doing wonderfully well.
I'm very proud.

923
01:06:36,355 --> 01:06:40,815
Mr. Devlin bothering you much?
Oh, no, darling.
He's trying to drown his sorrow.

924
01:06:41,928 --> 01:06:43,725
Champagne Cork Pops

925
01:07:03,516 --> 01:07:05,916
Man Speaking In French

926
01:07:21,634 --> 01:07:25,365
Excuse me. I think I'll ask the
orchestra to play some Brazilian music.

927
01:07:25,471 --> 01:07:28,269
They've played waltzes all evening.
Go, my dear.

928
01:07:28,374 --> 01:07:30,604
Man Continues In French

929
01:07:49,462 --> 01:07:51,362
That's the door.
Right.

930
01:07:55,501 --> 01:07:58,664
I'll keep the garden door open,
and I'll tell you if anything happens.

931
01:08:01,474 --> 01:08:04,375
